# TZ-94 — Brutalist Architectural UI Refinement: Phase 2 (Component Enhancements)

**Дата:** 2026-07-11
**Статус:** ✅ DONE (4 компонента реализованы, typecheck 0 errors, 33 tests pass)
**Тип:** cross-cutting (component refactor + utility adoption)
**Приоритет:** высокий (continuation of TZ-93 brutalist architectural refinement)
**Phases:** 2/3 — это Phase 2 из 3-фазного плана. Phase 1 = TZ-93 ✅ DONE, Phase 3 = TZ-95.
**LAYER:** Phase 2 = **Layer 3 SERIAL** (each component in its own commit per TZ-90C pattern)
**Зависимости:** TZ-93 ✅ DONE (2 utilities: `.pi-tech-label`, `.pi-dashed-panel`) + TZ-93.1 ✅ DONE (rollback of `.pi-corner-marks`), Paper & Ink design system, TZ-90 (Dialog System polymorphic wrapper pattern)
**Источник:** `stitch_professional_desktop_crm_refinement (1).zip` — Google Stitch design export, analyzed in TZ-93 think phase.

**CONFLICT KEYS:**
  - frontend/src/app/shared/ui/pi-empty-state/pi-empty-state.component.ts        # C.1: wrap inner content in pi-dashed-panel
  - frontend/src/app/shared/ui/pi-empty-state/pi-empty-state.component.spec.ts   # C.1: update DOM queries
  - frontend/src/app/shared/ui/badge/badge.component.ts                         # C.2: hairline border + transparent bg refactor
  - frontend/src/app/shared/ui/badge/badge.component.spec.ts                    # C.3: update variant styling assertions
  - frontend/src/app/shared/ui/pi-table.component.ts                            # C.3: add numeric: boolean to ColumnDef
  - frontend/src/app/shared/ui/label/label.component.ts                         # C.4: decouple required from variant
  - frontend/src/app/shared/ui/label/label.component.spec.ts                    # C.4: update variant/required tests
  - frontend/src/app/shared/ui/form-field/form-field.component.ts               # C.4: default variant to eyebrow
  - frontend/src/app/shared/ui/form-field/form-field.component.spec.ts          # C.4: update FormField tests
  - frontend/src/app/pages/playground/theme-editor.page.ts                      # fixture update if needed for new demo

**Решения пользователя (зафиксированы):**
1. ✅ **PiEmptyState → Approach A**: wrap inner content in `<div class="max-w-sm mx-auto p-6 pi-dashed-panel">` inside the `<td>`. Avoids table border-collapse collision.
2. ⛔ **[RETIRED in TZ-93.1]** PiEmptyTile conditional corner marks removed (`.pi-corner-marks` utility rolled back). No TZ-94 changes needed for PiEmptyTile — component ships unchanged.
3. ✅ **PiBadge → merge `outline` + `secondary` visually** (keep `outline` as API alias for backward compat). All variants: hairline border + transparent bg + semantic text color.
4. ✅ **PiTable → explicit `numeric: boolean`** in `ColumnDef` (NOT proxy on `align === 'right'`). Decouples alignment from numeric.
5. ✅ **PiLabel/PiFormField → BREAKING change**: decouple `required` from `variant`. Extract `required` into standalone boolean input. Make `variant="eyebrow"` the default for FormField. Migrate all `<app-pi-label variant="required">` usages.
6. ✅ **Layer 3 SERIAL commit order** (least-risky first, breaking last):
   1. `feat(ui): [TZ-94] add numeric column support to PiTable for tabular-nums`
   2. `refactor(ui): [TZ-94] modernize PiBadge variants with hairline and transparent backgrounds`
   3. `refactor(ui): [TZ-94] wrap PiEmptyState content in pi-dashed-panel`
   4. `refactor(ui): [TZ-94] decouple PiLabel required state and map FormField defaults to eyebrow`

---

## 1. Цель

Применить 2 TZ-93 utility-classes (`.pi-tech-label`, `.pi-dashed-panel`) к существующим 24+ UI-компонентам проекта. Phase 2 фокусируется на 5 компонентах, которые получили наибольшую выгоду от architectural patterns:

- **PiEmptyState** — wrap inner content в `.pi-dashed-panel` для "dropzone" feel.
- **PiEmptyTile** — *(retired в TZ-93.1; no TZ-94 changes — component ships unchanged)*
- **PiBadge** — refactor всех variants к hairline border + transparent bg + semantic text.
- **PiTable** — add `numeric: boolean` flag к `ColumnDef` для `tabular-nums` treatment.
- **PiLabel** — decouple `required` от `variant`, default `variant="eyebrow"`.
- **PiFormField** — default to eyebrow labels, expose `labelVariant` input.

**Главный принцип:** Typecheck-strict, backward-compatible API где возможно, breaking change только для PiLabel/PiFormField (decoupling required — single source of truth для form typography).

---

## 2. Per-Component Adoption Strategy

> **Note on C-numbering:** C-numbers are stable component IDs (not commit order). They are preserved from the original TZ-94 spec to keep diffs small and historical anchors stable. The retired `~~C.2 — PiEmptyTile~~` section keeps its original number to avoid renumbering 3 surviving sections. Commit order is defined in §3 (the table); C-numbers are just for cross-referencing this document.

### C.3 (FIRST commit) — PiTable: add `numeric: boolean` flag

**Files:** `frontend/src/app/shared/ui/pi-table.component.ts`

**Why first:** Safest schema addition, immediately testable, no visual change without explicit opt-in.

**Changes:**

```typescript
// ColumnDef interface — ADD new field
export interface ColumnDef<T> {
  key: keyof T & string;
  label: string;
  sortable?: boolean;
  align?: 'left' | 'right' | 'center';
  width?: string;
  format?: (row: T) => string;
  cellClass?: string;
  accessor?: (row: T) => unknown;
  /** NEW: applies `tabular-nums` to <td> for monospace numeric alignment. */
  numeric?: boolean;
}

// Template — UPDATE <td> to bind tabular-nums
<td
  class="py-3 px-3 align-top tabular-nums"
  [class.tabular-nums]="col.numeric"
  [class.text-right]="col.align === 'right'"
  [class.text-center]="col.align === 'center'"
  [class]="col.cellClass ?? ''"
>
  {{ formatCell(col, row) }}
</td>
```

**Acceptance:**
- `ColumnDef.numeric` is optional, defaults to `false` (no visual change).
- When `numeric: true`, the `<td>` gets the `tabular-nums` utility class.
- Existing column definitions in operational pages (`/materials`, `/organizations`, etc.) continue to work unchanged.

**Test updates:** Add a new test in a new `pi-table.component.spec.ts` (currently no spec file exists) verifying:
- `numeric: true` adds `tabular-nums` class to `<td>`.
- `numeric: false` (or omitted) does NOT add `tabular-nums`.

---

### ~~C.2 — PiEmptyTile: conditional corner marks~~ (RETIRED in TZ-93.1)

PiEmptyTile was originally planned as the second commit (C.2) for TZ-94, with conditional `.pi-corner-marks` applied at `sizePx() >= 80`. After the TZ-93.1 rollback of `.pi-corner-marks`, there are no remaining TZ-94 changes for PiEmptyTile. The component ships unchanged from TZ-46.

The conditional logic in the original spec was:
- Default `sizePx=48` (catalog thumbnail): NO corner marks (anti-noise).
- `sizePx >= 80` (large tiles, e.g. hero placeholders): corner marks visible.

The threshold-based gating was a workaround, not a fix — it just hid the problem in smaller tiles, not solved the aesthetic concern. With `.pi-corner-marks` removed entirely, the gate is moot.

---

### C.2 (SECOND commit) — PiBadge: hairline border + transparent bg refactor

**Files:** `frontend/src/app/shared/ui/badge/badge.component.ts` + `.spec.ts`

**Why second:** Visual refactor (intentional refresh), API backward-compatible. `outline` and `secondary` become visually merged but type union preserved.

**Changes:**

```typescript
// VARIANT_CLASS — REFACTOR: all hairline border + transparent bg
const VARIANT_CLASS: Record<PiBadgeVariant, string> = {
  default: 'bg-transparent hairline border-sunrise-warm text-sunrise-warm',
  secondary: 'bg-transparent hairline border-rule text-ink',
  outline: 'bg-transparent hairline border-rule text-muted-foreground', // visually merged with secondary
  destructive: 'bg-transparent hairline border-destructive text-destructive',
};

// Note: 'hairline' is already 1px solid var(--color-rule). Adding border-{color}
// override tints the border. Text carries semantic meaning.
```

**Acceptance:**
- All 4 variants use `bg-transparent` + `hairline` + semantic border + semantic text.
- `outline` and `secondary` are visually similar (both `border-rule text-X`) — acceptable since `outline` is a legacy alias.
- No new inputs, no breaking API changes.
- `computedClass()` still works with all 4 variant values.

**Test updates:** Update `badge.component.spec.ts` styling assertions:
- `variant="default"` should NOT have `bg-sunrise-warm` (was solid fill).
- `variant="destructive"` should NOT have `bg-destructive` (was solid fill).
- All variants should have `bg-transparent` + `hairline`.
- `variant="outline"` and `variant="secondary"` should have visually similar classes (border-rule + bg-transparent).

---

### C.1 (THIRD commit) — PiEmptyState: wrap in pi-dashed-panel

**Files:** `frontend/src/app/shared/ui/pi-empty-state/pi-empty-state.component.ts` + `.spec.ts`

**Why third:** DOM restructuring (adds wrapper div), but no breaking change. Visual treatment is the centerpiece of the "architectural empty state" pattern.

**Changes:**

```typescript
// Template — WRAP inner content in max-w-sm + pi-dashed-panel
template: `
  <tr data-test="empty-state-row">
    <td
      [attr.colspan]="colspan()"
      [attr.role]="state() === 'error' ? 'alert' : 'status'"
      [attr.aria-live]="state() === 'loading' ? 'polite' : null"
      class="py-12 px-4 text-center text-muted-foreground"
    >
      <div class="max-w-sm mx-auto p-6 pi-dashed-panel
                  flex flex-col items-center gap-1">
        <span class="eyebrow text-sunrise-warm">{{ eyebrow() }}</span>
        <span class="text-sm">{{ message() }}</span>
      </div>
    </td>
  </tr>
`
```

**Why max-w-sm + mx-auto:** Without max-width, the dashed panel would stretch to fill the entire row width, losing the "centered dropzone" feel. `max-w-sm` (24rem / 384px) constrains the visual treatment to a centered, intentional empty state.

**Acceptance:**
- The empty state has a centered, max-384px-wide panel with a dashed border (no corner marks — rolled back in TZ-93.1).
- The outer `<tr>` / `<td>` structure is preserved (no table layout breakage).
- `state="error"` still gets `role="alert"`, `state="loading"` still gets `aria-live="polite"`.

**Test updates:** Update `pi-empty-state.component.spec.ts`:
- Update DOM query helpers: `cell()` should find `<td>`, then the inner div is the `.pi-dashed-panel`.
- Add assertion: the inner div has class `pi-dashed-panel max-w-sm`.
- Existing tests for `colspan`, `message`, `eyebrow`, `state` continue to pass.

---

### C.4 (FOURTH commit, BREAKING) — PiLabel + PiFormField: decouple required, default to eyebrow

**Files:**
- `frontend/src/app/shared/ui/label/label.component.ts` + `.spec.ts`
- `frontend/src/app/shared/ui/form-field/form-field.component.ts` + `.spec.ts`

**Why last:** This is the ONLY breaking change in TZ-94. Doing it last means the other 3 commits can ship independently if C.4 needs to be reverted or deferred.

**Changes (PiLabel):**

```typescript
// BEFORE:
export type LabelVariant = 'default' | 'eyebrow' | 'mono' | 'required';

// AFTER: remove 'required' from variant union
export type LabelVariant = 'default' | 'eyebrow' | 'mono';

// NEW: standalone required input
export class LabelComponent {
  readonly variant = input<LabelVariant>('default');
  readonly required = input<boolean>(false);  // NEW
  readonly htmlFor = input<string | null>(null);

  readonly computedClass = computed(() => {
    const v = this.variant();
    switch (v) {
      case 'eyebrow':
        return 'eyebrow';
      case 'mono':
        return 'font-mono text-xs text-ink';
      case 'default':
      default:
        return 'text-sm font-medium text-ink';
    }
  });
}

// Template — asterisk is now controlled by required() input
template: `
  <label [attr.for]="htmlFor()" [class]="computedClass()">
    <ng-content />
    @if (required()) {
      <span aria-hidden="true" class="text-destructive ml-0.5">*</span>
    }
  </label>
`
```

**Changes (PiFormField):**

```typescript
// Template — change default label variant to eyebrow
template: `
  <div class="flex flex-col gap-form-row">
    @if (label()) {
      <app-pi-label
        variant="eyebrow"          <!-- CHANGED from "required ? 'required' : 'default'" -->
        [required]="required()"
        [htmlFor]="htmlFor()"
      >{{ label() }}</app-pi-label>
    }
    <div class="block">
      <ng-content />
    </div>
    @if (error()) {
      <span class="text-xs text-destructive" role="alert">{{ error() }}</span>
    } @else if (hint()) {
      <span class="text-xs text-muted-foreground">{{ hint() }}</span>
    }
  </div>
`

// OPTIONAL: expose labelVariant for per-form-field override
readonly labelVariant = input<LabelVariant>('eyebrow');  // NEW (default: eyebrow)
```

**Migration path (for all operational pages):**

```bash
# Find all usages of <app-pi-label variant="required">
grep -rn 'variant="required"' frontend/src/app --include='*.ts'

# Replace with the decoupled form:
#   variant="required"  →  variant="eyebrow" [required]="true"
#   variant="default"   →  variant="eyebrow" (no required prop needed)
```

**Acceptance:**
- `PiLabel` no longer has `'required'` in `LabelVariant` union (compile error in existing `<app-pi-label variant="required">` usages).
- `PiLabel.required` is a new boolean input (defaults to `false`).
- `PiFormField` defaults to `variant="eyebrow"` for labels (editorial typography becomes the form default).
- `<app-pi-label variant="eyebrow" [required]="true">` works for required fields with eyebrow style + asterisk.
- All operational pages (login, materials, organizations, dictionaries, etc.) are migrated to the new API.

**Test updates:**

`label.component.spec.ts`:
- REMOVE test for `variant="required"` (no longer in type).
- ADD test for `required=true` showing the asterisk span.
- ADD test for `variant="eyebrow"` + `required=true` showing eyebrow + asterisk.
- Existing tests for `default`, `eyebrow`, `mono` continue to pass.

`form-field.component.spec.ts` (currently doesn't exist — add it):
- ADD test verifying default label variant is `eyebrow`.
- ADD test verifying `required=true` propagates the asterisk to the label.

