## 3. Layer 3 SERIAL Commit Order

Per the user's explicit request: "Layer 3 SERIAL (each component in its own commit per TZ-90C pattern)".

| # | Commit | Component | Risk | Visual Change | API Change |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| 1 | `feat(ui): [TZ-94] add numeric column support to PiTable for tabular-nums` | PiTable | Low | None (opt-in) | Backward-compatible (`numeric?: boolean`) |
| 2 | `refactor(ui): [TZ-94] modernize PiBadge variants with hairline and transparent backgrounds` | PiBadge | Medium | All variants refresh | Backward-compatible (type union unchanged) |
| 3 | `refactor(ui): [TZ-94] wrap PiEmptyState content in pi-dashed-panel` | PiEmptyState | Medium | Centered dropzone panel | None (DOM restructuring only) |
| 4 | `refactor(ui): [TZ-94] decouple PiLabel required state and map FormField defaults to eyebrow` | PiLabel + PiFormField | High | All form labels become eyebrow style | **BREAKING** (variant="required" removed) |

**Rationale for order:**
- Commit 1 is a safe addition (no visual change without opt-in, no API breakage).
- Commit 2 is a visual refresh but API-stable.
- Commit 3 is a visual addition but DOM-restructure (adds wrapper, doesn't break existing).
- Commit 4 is the breaking change — ship last so if it needs to be reverted, the other 3 can ship independently.

---

## 4. Risks and Tradeoffs

| Риск | Вероятность | Митигация |
|---|---|---|
| PiBadge visual refactor surprises existing users (solid fills → hairline borders) | Medium | Document in commit body. The `outline` variant already uses hairline, so the pattern is familiar. `secondary` and `outline` are visually merged (acceptable per thinker). |
| PiEmptyState wrapper div breaks table layout if `max-w-sm` is too narrow | Low | `max-w-sm` is 384px — well above the minimum readable width for an empty state message. Tables wider than 384px will center the panel. |
| PiLabel `variant="required"` removal breaks operational pages at compile time | High (guaranteed) | Project-wide find-and-replace: `variant="required"` → `variant="eyebrow" [required]="true"`. TypeScript will surface every call site. Migrate as part of the same commit. |
| PiFormField default to `eyebrow` changes form visual rhythm | Medium | Editorial typography becomes the canonical form label style. This aligns with Paper & Ink's "structural rigor" goal. |
| PiTable `numeric: true` requires adopter opt-in per column | Low | Existing columns continue to work without `numeric: true`. New columns can opt in for tabular-nums. |
| Tests break after DOM restructuring (PiEmptyState) | Medium | Update DOM query helpers in spec. Inner div is now the `.pi-dashed-panel`. |

